freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Lite cough. While my breathing is clear, with no wheezing my upper respiratory feels as though it is being recalibrated.

Yes. While I am feeling well at this time, on or about Wednesday, 3/3, I began to notice a change with respect to my lungs. I've encountered no difficulty with breathing, but Wednesday (3/3), Thursday (3/4), and Friday (3/5), I experienced a slight pain in my chest, much like when one is battling a respiratory cold. On Saturday (3/6) and today (3/7), the pain went away. As a lifelong asthmatic, I felt as though my lungs were being strengthened to fight COVID-19. It was as if the vaccine discovered my vulnerability, and was working to make my lungs stronger.
